thread.title: De Pere, Bay Port keep season going

title: De Pere, Bay Port keep season going
text:
Rdp: De Pere, Bay Port keep season going Press-Gazette Media 11:10 p.m. CDT October 22, 2015 Bay Port’s Alexa Schroeder (6) reacts after the Pirates score a point against Green Bay Preble during Thursday night’s WIAA Division 1 regional volleyball at Bay Port. (Photo: Evan Siegle/Press-Gazette Media) 
DE PERE – The third-seeded De Pere volleyball team cruised into a WIAA Division 1 regional final with a 25-17, 25-9, 25-14 home win over Appleton West in semifinal action on Thursday. 
Liz Nies had nine kills, Sydney Otto had 13 digs and three service aces and Lexi Cerrato had 10 digs and five aces for De Pere. Caroline Zehren added 14 assists. 
Bay Port 3, G.B. Preble 0 
SUAMICO – Paige Hostetler led a strong offensive attack for the sixth-seeded Pirates in a 25-23, 25-22, 25-17 home victory. 
Hostetler had 11 kills, Alexa Schrieder had nine and Natalie Englebert added eight more for Bay Port. 
Marva McGinnity had 25 assists and Englebert also had 10 digs in the win. 
Preble stats were not submitted. 
Appleton East 3, G.B. West 0 
APPLETON – The Wildcats were knocked out with a 25-10, 25-8, 25-13 defeat to the No. 3 seed. 
Julia Verhaagh led West with eight digs and two kills. Katelyn Leiden also had three digs, four assists and one kill. 
G.B. Southwest 3, Ashwaubenon 2 
The Trojans rallied from two sets down, and needed extra points in the fifth-and-deciding set to overcome the Jaguars in dramatic fashion, 11-25, 22-25, 25-22, 25-23, 17-15. 
Kimberly 3, G.B. East 0 
KIMBERLY – The Red Devils couldn’t pull off the upset in the Valley, suffering a 25-10, 25-8, 25-13 defeat. 
Kaukauna 3, Pulaski 0 
KAUKAUNA – Pulaski was dropped in straight sets to end its season, 25-18, 25-14, 25-9. 
Division 2 
G.B. Notre Dame 3, Peshtigo 0 
Grace Campbell slammed 13 kills to lead the top-seeded Tritons to victory 25-21, 25-12, 25-14. 
Corinne Meglic recorded 39 assists and Maureen Schick made 23 digs for Notre Dame (35-5). 
Teja Tonn had 10 kills and four blocks to lead the Bulldogs. Amanda Majewski made 14 digs and Ashley Dudka had 20 assists. 
Wrightstown 3, Denmark 0 
DENMARK –The third-seeded Tigers knocked off the second-seeded Vikings in straight sets, 25-17, 27-25, 26-24. 
Brooke Linzmeier paced Wrightstown with 26 assists and 10 digs, while Danielle Nennig had 13 kills and 15 digs, Carlie Servais had two aces with 10 kills and Lindsay Lemke had two blocks and 10 kills. 
Denmark was led by Ashley Leiterman with 12 kills and three blocks, Leanne Habeck with 26 assists and nine digs and Olivia Peters with 25 digs. 
Lux.-Casco 3, West De Pere 0 
LUXEMBURG – The top-seeded Spartans advanced with a decisive 25-9, 25-18, 25-11 home victory. 
Megan Cannon made 38 assists, seven digs and two aces to lead Luxemberg-Casco. Haley Yagodinski also had 15 kills with four blocks. Alexis Dorner and Olivia Boney each had 10 kills. Allie Byrne contributed with 14 digs. 
Seymour 3, Oconto Falls 0 
SEYMOUR – The second-seeded Thunder swept the Panthers in straight sets, 25-17, 25-17, 27-25. 
Jaclyn Zahn had nine kills and eight blocks for Seymour. Emma Ellis and Jenna Krause combined for 13 kills and 13 digs. Ellis also contributed with 18 assists. 
Emily Kilmer had 13 kills and 13 digs for the Panthers. Mikaela Thomson chipped in with 20 assists. 
Division 3 
Witt.-Birn. 3, Oconto 1 
WITTENBERG – Carlee Behnke slammed 20 kills but it wasn’t enough for the Blue Devils as they lost 19-25, 25-22, 25-20, 25-15. 
Kelly Stewart also had 10 kills and 11 digs for Oconto. Becky Berth made 30 assists and Aleah Williams had five kills with four blocks. 
Bonduel 3, Wabeno/Laona 1 
BONDUEL – The second-seeded Bears rallied after losing the first set for a 22-25, 25-18, 25-16, 26-24 win to move on. 
Miranda Schmidt led Bonduel with 22 assists and two aces. Danee Collier made 20 digs and Hayley Sorenson had 11 blocks. Hayley Tues slammed 13 kills. 
Man. Lutheran 3, Gibraltar 0 
MANITOWOC – Third-seeded Gibraltar fell via a sweep to the No. 2 Lancers, 25-21, 25-23, 25-17. 
Division 4 
Suring 3, Gillett 0 
The top-seeded Eagles moved on with a 25-12, 25-18, 25-19 victory over their Marinette & Oconto Conference rivals. 
Kate Stegeman and Hailey Thomson each had five hills, while Azee Vanbellinger had 26 digs and Courtney Heimerl had 14 asists and nine digs for Suring. 
For Gillett, Jessica Anderson had 11 assists and six service aces, while Victoria Loberger had six kills and Erin Balthazor added 11 digs. 
NEW Lutheran 3, Sheb. Lutheran 2 
The second-seeded Blazers needed five sets to survive against the sixth-seeded Crusaders, but remained alive in the playoffs with a 26-24, 20-25, 22-25, 25-7, 15-4 
Emily Bukowski had 14 kills, 26 digs, 20 service points and three aces for the N.E.W. Lutheran. Rachel Toenjes added 13 kills, 13 digs, 18 service points, five blocks and five aces. Abbie Viegut also had 10 kills and 39 assists. Morgan Meerstein contributed with 33 assists and 13 digs. 
Hilbert 3, Sevastopol 1 
HILBERT – The Pioneers took the first set before the top-seeded Wolves rebounded for a 21-25, 25-19, 25-19, 25-18 win. 
Elcho 3, Niagara 1 
ELCHO – The Badgers won the first set handily, but couldn’t keep up the momentum in a 10-25, 25-14, 25-22, 25-14 loss. 
WIAA VOLLEYBALL TOURNAMENT
